The paper deals with the task of continuous authentication on mobile devices using deep convolutional neural networks. The primary focus is on attribute detection, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of multi-task learning, which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.MM). The task of authentication involves security and privacy concerns, which are addressed in the cryptography (cs.CR) sub-category. The paper also discusses the performance of the proposed architecture, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Lastly, the paper discusses the deployment of the architecture on a mobile device, which falls under the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
